                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18130714-46-defend528 t18130714-46-deflabel278"></join>.</p>
               <p>- MILLS. I am a servant to Mr. Flemming's, pawnbroker, No. 90, Newgate-street. I produce a bed, pillow, bolster, and pillow-cases. I took in the pillow and bolster of the prisoner myself. I cannot say who pawned the bed.</p>
               <p>Q. to Mrs. Allen. Can you swear to the pillow and bolster - A. I can; they are mine.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I have nothing to say. I throw myself on the mercy of the court.</p>
               <p>GUILTY, aged 35.</p>
